AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - BOTSWANA
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Tue, 3 Aug 1999
From: Chan Yow Cheong <chanyowcheong@pacific.net.sg>
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for Asia
Source: O.I.E. Disease Information Periodical, 30 Jul 1999, Vol. 12 No. 29
<http://www.oie.int/info/A_info.htm>

Date of last previously reported outbreak: November 1987.
Emergency report
-------------------------
Text of an e-mail received on 26 July 1999 from Dr Motshudi V. Raborokgwe,
Director of Animal Health and Production, Ministry of Agriculture, Gaborone:
Report date: 13 July 1999.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 4 June 1999.
Estimated date of first infection: 31 May 1999.
Outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Sterglingh (22 56' 41" S - 27 54' 44" E), Tuli Block 1 farm
Description of affected population: pigs in a fenced commercial
cattle-producing farm.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible: 40
cases: 36
deaths: 36
destroyed: 0
slaughtered: 4

Diagnosis: pigs were dying in large numbers, showing inappetence,
recumbency and nervous signs.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: pigs had broken through the fence
and mixed with warthogs.
B. Other epidemiological details: there is no adjacent pig farm.
Control measures during reporting period: movement restriction on pigs has
been imposed into and out of the affected property.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
...................tg/es
